President Uhuru Kenyatta will on Thursday chair the first Azimio La Umoja One Kenya coalition council meeting set to be held at Kenyatta International Convention Centre. ODM leader Raila Odinga will attend the meeting. The meeting is slated to begin at 7:30 am. "The Azimio La Umoja Coalition Party flag-bearer and ODM party leader Hon Raila Odinga will attend the first AzimioCouncil meeting tomorrow Thursday 21st, April 2022," Raila's presidential campaigns press secretary Dennis Onsarigo said in a statement to the newsroom. The meeting brings on board the council membership. Uhuru is the chair of the council while Raila is the Azimio party leader. Council members include Wiper leader Kalonzo Musyoka, Narc-Kenya leader Martha Karua, Governor Ali Hassan Joho,  KANU chairman Gideon Moi, NARC leader Charity Ngilu, DAP-K party leader Wafula Wamunyinyi, Muranga Woman Representative Sabina Chege, Abdi Noor Omar Farah and Taveta MP Naomi Shaban. Suna East Member of Parliament Junet Mohammed is the Secretary-General of the National  Executive Council of the coalition party. He will sit at the council by virtue of his position.